  "text": "1,2 Based on a study in the United States, it concluded that a family history of osteoporosis is a significant and independent risk factor for osteoporosis in women aged 35 years and older. [CITATION_1] Another research in theUnited States conducted by Meadows et al. [CITATION_2] , discovers that out of the 1.800 women who have undergone treatment for osteoporosis, about half have reported a family history of osteoporosis.",
